richard hutton , writing in the spectator , in 1863 , observed that " [ t]he greatest artistic purpose of the story is to trace out the conflict between liberal culture and the more passionate form of the christian faith in that strange era , which has so many points of resemblance with the present".richard hutton , the spectator , 18 july 1863 in george eliot : godless woman by brian spittles ( basingstoke , hampshire ; london : macmillan press , 1993 )

